  "text": "Single-incision slings (SIS) were optimized to overcome these complications. TVT-Secur was the first single-incision device, and was developed in 2006. This device can be placed using a retropubic or \"U\" approach, or a transobturator-like \"hammock\" approach [CITATION_1] . The innovation was based on the use of shorter polypropylene laser-cut tape (8 cm × 1 cm) through a single vaginal incision in order to avoid the retropubic space, obturator foramen, or groin muscles, and their related nerves and blood vessels.",
